                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/19265: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Casablanca (<persName type="to">Russell</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 4, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. For Murphy from Dunn. Find great interest in subject of your letter of
                    January 9 to me. When you see Hibbard<note n="50" xml:id="d241fn50">Frederick P.
                        Hibbard, en route to his post as Counselor of Legation in Liberia.</note>
                    give him as much specific and detailed information on subject as possible and I
                    will endeavor to inform you of our policy. [Dunn.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
